  "help": {
    "title": "Need help?",
    "aiKeysQ": "How does AI generation work (Gemini, Qwen)?",
    "aiKeysA": "Blackmind uses Gemini as the primary provider (up to 3 keys tried in order), with Qwen as an automatic fallback. Generate content two ways: type a topic in the chat, or import an existing document via the + menu → Import from Google Workspace to turn it into a structured course. Set your provider keys in the project's environment variables — without one, generation won't work.",
    "exportQ": "How do I export my course?",
    "exportA": "From a course's \"...\" menu, choose Download course for a PDF or DOCX, or Open in Google Docs if your Google account is connected.",
    "googleDriveQ": "How do I link my Google Drive account?",
    "googleDriveA": "In Settings → Integrations, click Connect Google. Once connected, you can open your courses directly in Google Docs and save media to your Drive.",
    "accessibilityQ": "Where are the accessibility options?",
    "accessibilityA": "In Settings → Accessibility: dyslexia-friendly font, high contrast, audio reading, text size and more, applied instantly across the whole app.",
    "workspacesQ": "How do I collaborate with my team?",
    "workspacesA": "Create a workspace in the Workspaces tab, then use Share to a workspace or Invite collaborators from a course's menu.",
    "monetizeQ": "How do I monetize my course?",
    "monetizeA": "From a course's \"...\" menu, choose Sell and set a price — it's then listed on the Marketplace where other users can buy it."
  },
